Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.58,0:15:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't an Itsuu
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.88,0:15:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,An end wait on 7 Sou?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.25,0:15:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Why on earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.81,0:16:10.01,small - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1104,528)}10th Game\NSouth Hand 3
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.25,0:16:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.11,0:16:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm in Tenpai
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.95,0:16:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,If I discard the 5 Pin it's a 1/4 Pin wait
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.28,0:16:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Or if I discard the 3 Pin it's a 2 Pin/White dragon two-pair wait
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.15,0:16:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever I do my two White Dragons are Dora, plus an Iipeikou
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.45,0:16:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and If I Riichi it's certainly more than Mangan
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.48,0:16:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,As there's already two White Dragons discarded...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.05,0:16:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,so my decision is straightforward
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.65,0:16:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.95,0:16:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,With such a readable wait
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.65,0:16:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't be able to get a direct hit
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.85,0:16:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Naturally the West team won't deal into it
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.25,0:16:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But I wasn't expecting that from the start
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.58,0:16:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I WILL DRAW IT
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.95,0:17:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,IT CAN'T BE!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.88,0:17:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,FIVE white dragon tiles???
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.41,0:17:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the west team
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.91,0:17:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The West team mixed in an extra White from the start
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.71,0:17:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But... for what purpose?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.01,0:17:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it insurance?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.48,0:17:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're at a disadvantage, just announcing there's 5 white tiles...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.81,0:17:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,will invalidate the hand
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.11,0:17:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to be kidding
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.11,0:17:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no reason why I have to play along with this
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.61,0:17:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,BUT, why should I throw away my advantage?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.48,0:17:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,If I complete my hand, I win
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.08,0:17:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,If I draw it I WIN
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.61,0:18:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,South and North wind tiles?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.91,0:18:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I can understand him playing around my Riichi
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.98,0:18:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,but having a North and South wind floating in your hand so late in the game is unusual
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.38,0:18:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,A Kokusi Musou?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.98,0:18:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, more and more it's looking that way
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.38,0:18:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, it is amusing
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.78,0:18:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,He may be in tenpai but I can't lose if he's waiting on a White Dragon that will never come
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.71,0:18:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got the other two he's waiting for
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.18,0:18:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if Harada thinks there's two remaining
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.18,0:18:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just impossible for him to get one
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.58,0:18:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And if it's impossible, the chances he deals into my hand increases
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.91,0:19:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,More and more this White Dragon
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.81,0:19:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,looks like a poison mixed in to benefit Harada
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.78,0:19:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and ironically that poison
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.51,0:19:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,is now running through Harada's own veins
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.51,0:19:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Any moment now...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.71,0:19:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,A SIXTH WHITE DRAGON???
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.55,0:19:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,YOU HAVE GOT TO BE FUCKING KIDDING
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.55,0:19:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Enough with the fucking cheating already
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.68,0:20:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Whats the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.18,0:20:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,If it doesn't complete your hand get rid of it, or else...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.08,0:20:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,have you forgotten how to discard?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.58,0:20:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,OH, a White Dragon?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.28,0:20:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.31,0:20:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.98,0:20:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Kokusi Musou
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.68,0:20:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,HA HA HA HA HA!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.11,0:20:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And with that, the game is over!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.18,0:20:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop fucking around,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.61,0:20:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to accept a game like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.11,0:20:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,LOOK!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.81,0:20:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What I discarded was the SIXTH White Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.81,0:20:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,A mess like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.58,0:21:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You think I'd let an illegal move like this go through!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.15,0:21:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Illegal?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.15,0:21:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But you yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.78,0:21:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't you already accept that Illegal move?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.41,0:21:15.41,Default,,0,0,0,,When you had two Whites in your hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.41,0:21:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You drew the 5th White right after declaring Riichi
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.31,0:21:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus at that time,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.81,0:21:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You should have noticed something off with the game
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.68,0:21:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you say anything THEN?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.38,0:21:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Apparently, when it suits your purposes...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.51,0:21:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you accept what's illegal
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.98,0:21:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,but when it's not to your advantage you go around shouting "illegal, illegal!"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.58,0:21:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, that kind of play is simply not acceptable
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.81,0:21:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.28,0:21:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you think so, Akagi?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.38,0:21:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly, it's as you say
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.38,0:21:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,A-Akagi
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.21,0:22:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But Harada,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.38,0:22:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite that, I'm quite sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.38,0:22:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,you haven't won
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.81,0:22:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.61,0:22:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,If you accept there are 6 White Dragon tiles
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.01,0:22:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Naturally this game is an exception
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.41,0:22:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you accept that exception
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.81,0:22:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll have to accept my exception from the rules as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.35,0:22:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.01,0:22:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Head Bump
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.01,0:22:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Head bump he says?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.45,0:22:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,HA HA HA HA
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.35,0:22:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,ARE YOU FUKKIN RETARDED?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.11,0:22:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The kid discarded a WHITE DRAGON
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.41,0:22:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You're waiting on a 2/5 Sou (bamboo) or a 5 Pin (dots)
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.28,0:22:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, on the surface
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.15,0:22:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,HUNH?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.45,0:22:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,If there's 6 White Dragons...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.78,0:22:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That means there were tiles left out of the game
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.91,0:22:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably three tiles of two types
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.18,0:22:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I say that White that Hiroyuki discarded isn't a White at all
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.28,0:22:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I say it was destined to be a missing tile I could declare Ron on
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.91,0:23:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Missing tile?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.08,0:23:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.71,0:23:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That tile is precisely
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.38,0:23:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,a 5 Sou (5 bamboo)
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.88,0:23:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,If you examine the left over tiles in that Mahjong case
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.18,0:23:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll soon know if it's among the few left over tiles
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.38,0:23:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And if there's a 5 Sou among them...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.98,0:23:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll accept my head bump
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.81,0:23:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And as it's merely a Tanyao hand
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.31,0:23:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the game will simply continue
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.05,0:23:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But if there isn't a 5 Sou in that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.91,0:23:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You're out of bounds
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.91,0:23:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and the point penalty KNOCKS YOU THE FUCK OUT!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.51,0:23:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,If you agree to that...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.61,0:23:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll accept the bet
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.55,0:23:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,No problem
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.38,0:23:48.38,Default - top,,0,0,0,,Akagi
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.38,0:23:49.88,Default - top,,0,0,0,,Please. Don't do it
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.88,0:23:51.61,Default - top,,0,0,0,,The tiles the West team swapped
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.61,0:23:53.98,Default - top,,0,0,0,,Only two types of tiles out of 34 in Mahjong
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.98,0:23:58.41,Default - top,,0,0,0,,Choosing just the 5 sou is not a gamble you're likely to win!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.41,0:24:00.91,Default - top,,0,0,0,,I'm the one that dealt into Harada's hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.91,0:24:02.91,Default - top,,0,0,0,,Hiro,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.91,0:24:06.21,Default - top,,0,0,0,,It's gone too far already
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.21,0:24:07.18,Default - top,,0,0,0,,Hunh?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.18,0:24:09.61,Default - top,,0,0,0,,I declared a Ron
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.61,0:24:12.38,Default - top,,0,0,0,,There's no turning back
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.38,0:24:16.28,Default - top,,0,0,0,,Whether or not your White should have been a 5 Sou...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.28,0:24:19.68,Default - top,,0,0,0,,Is the question at hand
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.05,0:24:22.71,Default - top,,0,0,0,,BUT
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.71,0:24:24.71,Default - top,,0,0,0,,Hiroyuki,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.58,0:24:31.61,Default - top,,0,0,0,,Akagi Shigeru himself has said as much
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.61,0:24:34.61,Default - top,,0,0,0,,There's no taking it back
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.58,0:24:39.61,Default - top,,0,0,0,,We can only watch now
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.41,0:25:01.61,Default - white - top,,0,0,0,,Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.41,0:24:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi has survived!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.48,0:24:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What I'm afraid of is becoming what I'm not
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.41,0:25:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't avert your eyes from anything real
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.01,0:25:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The way forward opens!
